<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-11-03T11:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-11-03T11:45:00-05:00" n="601" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/6841: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-11-03T11:00:00-05:45">November 3, 1930—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 12:30 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>139. Congressional elections were held throughout Nicaragua yesterday
                            without disorder. Returns indicate important gains by the Liberals in
                            both branches of Congress.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>